    Multidisciplinary Neuroscientific Technologies Ltd

    --- MISSION STATEMENT ---

    (1) Exploring and experimenting with computing engineering hardware & software technologies.

    (2) Exploring how these can be merged with biosciences/neurosciences at all levels of structural organisation.

    (3) Developing computational models of neurobiological systems; and implementing neural approaches to computing.

    (4) Applying these resources to practical ways of solving real-world everyday-life complex problems.

          Welcome to BioNeuroTech!

          ​

           

          BioNeuroTech (BNT) is currently an open-source platform of code and datasets, for basic prototyping and experimenting in the Computational Modelling of Neurobiological Systems and Neuro-Technologies. BNT aims to develop interactive computer-based programs.

           

          It uses various other resources & digital tools from other organizations, in order to develop these programs. It is based on independent and collaborative efforts.

          ​

          BNT aims to develop a wide range of products and services, while providing contributions to larger projects from other organizations.

          ​

          It is currently in its early stages of development.

          ​

          The 2030 Vision: Solving the most complex problems in Computational Neurosciences and Systems Biosciences (and many other fields), and creating novel revolutionary products and services for the future of humanity.

          ​

          ​

          The image gallery above displays some of the mini-projects that have been worked on.

          The video banner at the top ( references: ), is simply a visual representation

          of the '2030 Vision' projects, currently being researched.
